article.headline: Massachusetts 78, Siena 69
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. (AP) -- Rashaun Freeman had 23 points and 12 rebounds and Massachusetts used a 7-0 game-ending run to pull away for a 78-69 win over Siena on Friday night. Siena (4-4), which trailed by as many as 15 in the second half, pulled within 71-69 on a basket and free throw by Kojo Mensah with 1:33 to play. Chris Lowe hit a layup and two free throws to start the Minutemen's run. Stephane Lasme and James Life also hit a pair of free throws each for the final score. Life and Jeff Viggiano had 12 each for UMass (4-3) and Life finished with 10. Freeman was 7-of-10 from the field and 9-of-11 from the line. Mensah led Siena with 23 while Antoine Jordan had 18 and Tay Fisher 13. Lowe's steal and layup gave the Minutemen a 44-34 lead at halftime. Freeman's layup with 15:03 to go in the game gave UMass its largest lead of the game 54-39.
